1 Setup

1.1 Here’s the library you’ll need for this TP

library(ggplot2)
library(dplyr)
library(gapminder)

3 Plot

3.1 Here’s the plot of the gdpPercap with the lifeExp

4 Improvements

4.1 Try to determine which one is the outliers above

gapminder %>%
  filter(year=="1952", gdpPercap >= 60000) %>%
  group_by(country)
## # A tibble: 1 x 6
## # Groups:   country [1]
##   country continent  year lifeExp    pop gdpPercap
##   <fct>   <fct>     <int>   <dbl>  <int>     <dbl>
## 1 Kuwait  Asia       1952    55.6 160000   108382.

4.2 It’s Koweit in 1952, we erase him to have a better dataset

gapminder %>%
  filter(year=="1952", country!="Kuwait") %>%
  ggplot( aes(x=lifeExp, y=gdpPercap))  +
  geom_point()

4.3 With color it’s always better

gapminder %>%
  filter(year=="1952", country!="Kuwait") %>%
  ggplot( aes(x=lifeExp, y=gdpPercap, color=continent))  +
  geom_point()

4.4 With the appropriate size it’s better

gapminder %>%
  filter(year=="1952", country!="Kuwait") %>%
  ggplot( aes(x=lifeExp, y=gdpPercap, color=continent, size=pop))  +
  geom_point()

4.5 Interactive data

library(DT)

datatable(gapminder, rownames = FALSE, filter="top", options = list(pageLength = 5, scrollX=T) )
library(devtools)
install_github("holtzy/epuRate")
library(epuRate)
